--all
     commit all stage changes
-s
     add singed-off-by tag
-f
     specify input file as new commit message
--reset-author
    reset patch author
--author=
-m/--message
    add commit message
--amend
   amend existed commit.

--file=<file>/-F <file>
Take the commit message from the given file. Use - to read from
the message from the standard input.

-C/--resue-message=<commit>
reuse an existed commit.

-c/--reedit-message=<commit>
reedit existed log message.

--cleanup
stripe/default
whitespace-->this can keep # lines
verbatim --->do not change messages at all

--fixup=<commit>
Construct commit message for use with rebase --autosquash,
It is related to git-rebase.

